nk the import for `groovy.xml.DOMBuilder` is missing. The line using `mkp.'yield'('Fast ')` seems likely okay. The declaration for `private static final String CATALOG_XML` using triple single-quoted string continuation should work as well. I suspect that the dynamic property assignment in `QName bookName = namespace.book` is fine with the right casting. I also need to check the method overriding rules in Groovy regarding exceptions, as it has different requirements than Java.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering parser ambiguity**\\n\\nI'm pondering whether the line `assertThat(catalog.book.find { it.@id == 'b1' }.title.text())` might create some parser ambiguity. The direct access with `it.@id` requires a specific identifier, but using just `id` would be fine. However, inside the closure, comparing the GPathResult to a String seems okay. I should ensure I'm clear on this, as I wouldn't want any unexpected behavior in my code.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_f3xFY7fCG2aC1ANYMxTmiPec|fc_0e23996072bfb32b016a26bf22e3f88195a8688d6e9f9ca117", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/org.apache.groovy/groovy-xml/4.0.22 -type f -mmin -120 | sort | sed -n '1,200p'"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 916, "output": 1341, "cacheRead": 76288, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 78545, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780924162343, "responseId": "resp_0e23996072bfb32b016a26bf03164c8195adec10ac833bc9bb"}}
